\noindent{\bf Influence of LLM Pre-Training.}
Most books in our data are well discussed in online media (incl. movie/TV adaptations). The LLM implicitly taps into this contents by its parametric memory.
To assess the influence of LLM pre-training, we evaluate LLM-only vs. L3X {\em amp} for one of our books, the Void Trilogy. This book series is barely covered on the Web;
we invested great effort for compiling its ground truth.
The results show that LLM-only fails completely on this case: 12% recall with poor precision of ca. 5%, whereas our RAG-based {\em amp} gets 82% recall after Stage 1, and 34.1% R@P50 and 38.3% R@P80 
with default
{\em thr80} in Stage 2.